Rating: 3
This was really tasty and easy...filling enough for dinner too. I halved the crouton recipe, it made plenty, and also halved the oil in the vinaigrette recipe...I usually do that because I don't like oily salads and it makes it a little lighter. I just grilled two chicken breasts on the George Foreman & shredded them with a fork, so I didn't have to buy a whole chicken. I found perlini, which are pearl-size mozzarella balls, they were really cute!

